### Audit

Use `ito tasks` CLI commands for all task state changes (emits audit events automatically).
Avoid editing `tasks.md` directly, but if you do, run `ito audit reconcile --change {{ instructions.changeName }} --fix` immediately after.
Run `ito audit reconcile --change {{ instructions.changeName }}` before archiving.

### Ito Artifact Mutation

When you need to change Ito active-work artifacts for this change, use Ito's artifact mutation commands instead of direct file edits:

```bash
ito patch change {{ instructions.changeName }} proposal
ito write change {{ instructions.changeName }} design
ito patch change {{ instructions.changeName }} tasks
ito write change {{ instructions.changeName }} spec <capability>
```

- Use `ito patch` for targeted diffs against an existing artifact.
- Use `ito write` for complete replacement of an artifact's contents.
- Keep using ordinary file-edit tools for non-Ito project code.

